  "prompt": "Where do we get beef jerky or biltong in London?",
  "response": "London offers a good selection of places to buy beef jerky and biltong. Here are some options, broken down by type:\n\n**Specialty Shops & South African Stores (For Biltong Focus):**\n\n*   **The Savanna:** South African shop, often mentioned for good quality and variety of biltong.\n*   **Sanza:** Another South African store, well stocked with biltong, dro\u00ebwors, and other South African goodies.\n*   **Dassie Artisan:** Offers high-quality South African goods, including biltong.\n*   **Biltong St M\u00f4re:** Specializes in biltong.\n\n**General Food Stores & Delis (Good for both Beef Jerky and Biltong):**\n\n*   **Marks and Spencer (M&S):** Typically has a good selection of beef jerky and sometimes stocks biltong, often under their own brand.\n*   **Waitrose:** Similar to M&S, look for beef jerky and occasional biltong options.\n*   **Sainsbury's:** Another supermarket chain where you can usually find beef jerky.\n*   **Tesco:** As above, a reliable place to find beef jerky.\n*   **Fortnum & Mason:** A luxury department store with a food hall; they may have high-end beef jerky and potentially biltong. (Expect premium prices).\n\n**Butchers:**\n\n*   Some independent butchers might make their own biltong or jerky. It's worth calling local butchers to inquire.\n\n**Online Retailers (Delivering to London):**\n\n*   **Amazon UK:** A huge selection of beef jerky and biltong brands, available for delivery.\n*   **Yumbles:** An online marketplace for artisanal food producers. You might find independent biltong and jerky makers here.\n*   **Biltong and Jerky UK websites:** Many specialized online stores dedicated to biltong and jerky will deliver nationwide.\n\n**Things to Consider When Choosing:**\n\n*   **Type:**  Biltong is air-dried, marinated meat, often thicker than jerky and less sweet. Beef jerky is typically smoked or dried, and often has a sweeter, more heavily flavored marinade.\n*   **Ingredients:** Check the ingredients list for artificial additives, preservatives, and high sugar content if you are concerned about these.\n*   **Source:** If you prefer ethically sourced meat, look for grass-fed or organic options.\n*   **Price:** Prices can vary greatly depending on the brand, quality, and location.\n*   **Proximity:** Consider which stores are most convenient for you to visit.\n*   **Reviews:** If buying online, read customer reviews to get an idea of the quality and taste of the product.\n\n**To find a specific location near you:**\n\n1.  **Use Google Maps:** Search for \"biltong shop London\" or \"beef jerky shop London.\"\n2.  **Check websites:** Many of the stores listed above have websites with store locators.\n\nGood luck finding the perfect beef jerky or biltong!\n",
